Source-Available Portfolio Template License

Copyright (c) 2026 LaionFromNight / Lukasz Komur

This repository contains the source code for the interactive CV and developer
portfolio of Lukasz Komur.

The Project is made source-available so it can be viewed, studied, forked, and
used as a personal portfolio template under the conditions below.

1. Definitions

"Project" means this repository, including its source code, scripts, build
configuration, generated page system, static page renderer, PDF generation,
styles, documentation, and related files.

"Author" means Lukasz Komur / LaionFromNight.

"Personal Content" means any personal data, CV information, work history,
experience descriptions, images, names, profile links, contact details,
branding, Open Graph images, website identity, and other materials that identify
or describe Lukasz Komur.

"Configuration Files" means the JSON/data files intended for personal
customization, including but not limited to:

- src/data/cv.json
- src/data/seo.json
- src/data/cms.json

"Core System" means the application code, React components, layout system,
styling system, build scripts, static page renderer, CMS renderer, SEO pipeline,
PDF renderer, and project architecture.

2. Permissions

You may:

- view and study the Project source code;
- fork this repository;
- use the Project as a personal portfolio template;
- modify the Configuration Files to replace the Author's data with your own;
- replace public assets such as images, favicons, icons, and Open Graph images
  with your own assets;
- deploy your own personal version of the portfolio after replacing the
  Author's Personal Content;
- submit pull requests with improvements to the original repository.

3. Conditions

If you publish or deploy a fork of this Project, you must:

- replace the Author's Personal Content with your own content;
- not present the Author's identity, CV, experience, images, profile, links, or
  branding as your own;
- keep the copyright notice and this license in the repository;
- make it clear that your published version represents you, not Lukasz Komur.

The intended customization layer for personal forks is the Configuration Files
and personal/public assets.

4. Core System changes

You should not maintain a privately divergent version of the Core System for
redistribution as a separate template or product.

Changes to the Core System should be proposed to the original repository through
pull requests, especially changes to:

- application code;
- React components;
- layout or styling system;
- static page renderer;
- CMS/static page system;
- SEO/build pipeline;
- PDF renderer;
- scripts and build tooling;
- project architecture.

5. Restrictions

You may not:

- reuse, publish, or redistribute the Author's Personal Content as your own;
- impersonate the Author;
- publish a fork that may mislead others into believing it is the Author's
  official website or profile;
- sell, sublicense, or redistribute the Project as a competing portfolio
  template or product without written permission from the Author;
- remove copyright notices or this license from the repository;
- use the Author's name, image, links, CV, work history, experience, or branding
  to promote your own version.

6. Contributions

By submitting a pull request or other contribution to the original repository,
you agree that your contribution may be included in the Project under this same
license or a future license chosen by the Author.

